5e2b57e9-ec60-4ce7-8530-f7c6fcbd6a23.37dcfddc-5e0d-4583-afaa-319dfe465e5b.description=
This operation checks whether a string matches another string, using a specific matching rule. The "toMatch" input is the string that is checked for matching the "matchTo" expression. 

Inputs\:
    matchType - The type of match to perform.
Valid values\: Exact Match, Contains, Contains Once, Does Not Contain, Match All Words, Match No Words, Regex
Default value\: Exact Match
    toMatch - The string that is checked for matching.
    matchTo - The string to match against.
Example\: If "matchType" is “RegEx”, the "matchTo" input is a regular expression such as\: ^-?\d+(([\.,]\d+)?)+$. 
    ignoreCase - Specifies whether to ignore case when matching or not.
Valid values\: False, True
Default value\: False

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the string "Matches" if the "toMatch" string matches the "matchTo" string. Otherwise, it contains the string "Does Not Match".  

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

5e2b57e9-ec60-4ce7-8530-f7c6fcbd6a23.c4efafa6-f32c-44a8-832e-c667effd8721.description=
This operation evaluates the given "xpathExpression" and returns the results in a form of an iterator. This powerful operation can be used to retrieve XML Elements, Attributes, Text or filters based on element names, paths, attributes etc.  

Inputs\:
    xml - The XML in the form of a string.
    xpathExpression - The XPath expression to evaluate.
    parsingFeatures - The list of XML parsing features separated by new line (CRLF). The feature name - value must be separated by empty space. Setting specific features this field could be used to avoid XML security issues like "XML Entity Expansion injection" and "XML External Entity injection". To avoid aforementioned security issues we strongly recommend to set this input to the following values\: 
http\://apache.org/xml/features/disallow-doctype-decl true 
http\://xml.org/sax/features/external-general-entities false 
http\://xml.org/sax/features/external-parameter-entities false 
When the "http\://apache.org/xml/features/disallow-doctype-decl" feature is set to "true" the parser will throw a FATAL ERROR if the incoming document contains a DOCTYPE declaration.  
When the "http\://xml.org/sax/features/external-general-entities" feature is set to "false" the parser will not include external general entities. 
When the "http\://xml.org/sax/features/external-parameter-entities" feature is set to "false" the parser will not include external parameter entities or the external DTD subset. 
If any of the validations fails, the operation will fail with an error message describing the problem. 
Default value\:
http\://apache.org/xml/features/disallow-doctype-decl true
http\://xml.org/sax/features/external-general-entities false
http\://xml.org/sax/features/external-parameter-entities false

Results\:
    returnResult - Result evaluated from the XPath expression provided.
    type - The type of XML result returned.
Valid values\: ELEMENT, ATTRIBUTE, TEXT, OTHER
    attributeName - If the type of the result is "ATTRIBUTE", it will contain the name of the attribute.

Responses\:
    has more - Another result was in the list, and has been returned.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
    no more - No more results. This will only be returned once, then iteration restarts.

Notes\:
1. The World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) organization provides the XPath specification (http\://www.w3.org).
2. XML using default namespace is also supported by this operation.
3. An element from the default namespace can be retrieved using a location path.

Examples\:
   The following is a valid inputs example for working with a XML that uses default namespace. This example searches all "td" elements from the default namespace\:
    xml\: 

                

                    Apples
                    Bananas
                 

            

    path\: //*[namespace-uri()\="http\://www.w3.org/TR/html4/" and name()\="td"]
